ğŸš€ Getting Started
Prerequisites
To get the weather feature working, you will need an API key:

Get a free API key from OpenWeatherMap.

Open script.js and replace "YOUR_API_KEY_HERE" with your actual key.

Installation
Clone this repository:

Bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/digital-clock.git
Navigate to the project folder:

Bash
cd digital-clock
Open index.html in any modern web browser.

ğŸ§  What I Learned
Through this project, I practiced:

Asynchronous Programming: Using fetch with async/await to handle external data.

State Management: Toggling application logic based on user interaction.

Browser Storage: Using localStorage to create a seamless user experience.

CSS Flexbox: Mastering alignment and centering techniques.

